# FINAL_AKI_DOCUMENT

## Project Objective

Build a complete AKI (Acute Kidney Injury) trajectory pipeline on MIMIC data that supports:
- validated ingestion,
- medallion data layers on Iceberg,
- KDIGO labeling and feature engineering in batch,
- model training with Spark ML,
- and real-time simulation + scoring with Kafka and Spark Structured Streaming.

This document is the execution blueprint I will follow once you approve.

## Approved Data Scope

Current source files in `DATA/`:
- `Hospital Data/patients.csv`
- `Hospital Data/admissions-2.csv`
- `Hospital Data/labevents.csv`
- `Hospital Data/d_labitems.csv`
- `ICU DATA/icustays.csv`
- `ICU DATA/outputevents.csv`
- `ICU DATA/d_items.csv`

Readiness status from validation already completed:
- Required headers for KDIGO path are present.
- Strong creatinine coverage is present.
- Strong urine output coverage is present when using curated urine output itemids.
- Silver layer can fail if joins/filters are too broad (must be ICU-window constrained + curated itemids).

## Final Architecture

`Raw CSV -> GE Quality Gate #1 -> Iceberg Bronze -> dbt+Spark Silver -> Spark Batch Gold (KDIGO + features) -> Spark ML training -> Kafka replay/synthetic events -> Spark Streaming KDIGO/risk -> Iceberg Mart + monitoring`

Layer definitions:
- Bronze: raw validated records (minimal transformation)
- Silver: cleaned, standardized, ICU-joined clinical events
- Gold: hourly feature store + KDIGO labels + training dataset
- Mart: model outputs, live risk, QA tables, reporting tables

